# Planning 
UniWell health tracker that supports SDG3: Good Health and Well-Being.

# Mission
Our mission is to empower students to take control of their health by providing a simple, accessible, and reliable application.
The student health tracker will help users log daily health and receive personalized reminders, and access emergency support when needed. By fostering healthier rountines and ensuring timely medical assistance, 
our solution contributes to SDG3:Good Health and Well-Being, promoting a safer and more supportive university enviroment.

# Scope
The system will include:

Authentication: Secure login, Create a password, Password reset.

Health Records: Input and update daily water intake, sleep hours, exercise, and meals.

Data Visualization: Dashboard summaries and weekly averages.

Smart Reminders: Notifications when data is not recorded.

Admin Functions: Account management, health tips publishing, statistical reporting, and system monitoring.

# Tool Used:

Github -Version control, commits, and respository organization.

Trello -Agile board for backlog, sprint planning, and task tracking.

Prototype tool -Figma for ui and application developement.

# Team roles:
-Leader/Coordinator: Overseas progress, ensures deadlines are met.

-Designer: Creates diagrams, wireframes, and UI layouts.

-Developer: implements prototype features and commits code.

-Tester: Conducts testing, collect feedback, and reports bug.

-Documenter: prepares reports, organizes evidence, and updates Github.

# Sprints Goal:

Week 1(Sprint 1): Define vision, backlog, and requirments. Create initial diagrams.
-Leader: Organize trello board and backlog.
-Designer: Draft use case and class diagram.
-Documenter: Upload requirements and project plan.

Week2(Sprint 2): Develop prototype draft and upload design evidence.
- Developer: Build login and health record features.
- Designer: Create wireframes and UI mockups.
- Documenter: Upload design notes and screenshots.

Week3(Sprint 3): Conduct testing, collect feedback, and refine prototype.
- Tester: Run test cases and record results.
- Developer: Fix bugs and refine features.
- Documenter: Upload bug reports and feedback notes.

Week4(Sprint4): Finalize prototype, compile results, and prepare presentation.
- Leader:Coordinate final sprint tasks.
- Developer: Upload final prototype screenshots.
- Documenter: Prepare results summary and presentation slides.
- All: Ensure Github and Trello evidence are complete.
